SPAN 1413 - Introduction to Spanish I [TCCN: SPAN 1411]
Designed for the student having little or no previous exposure to the
Spanish language, this course concentrates on developing the ability to
understand, speak, read, and write in Spanish. Grammatical topics such
as the present and preterit verb tenses are presented along with an
introduction to Hispanic culture. Class conversation is a key element in
the instruction.
